Preheat broiler to high (or preheat oven to 500 degrees). Wash and dry all produce. Cut one @zucchini{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Trim ends from remaining @zucchini{1}, then grate into a #medium bowl{} using the large holes on a #box grater{}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed, separating whites from greens). Pick @oregano{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked from stems) from stems; discard stems and roughly chop leaves.

Place zucchini rounds on a #baking sheet{}. Toss with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (we'll use more later). Broil until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. (TIP: Watch the zucchini carefully, as it may brown quickly.) Transfer zucchini to a #small bowl{}. Reserve baking sheet for flatbreads. Adjust oven temperature to 450 degrees.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add @Italian chicken sausage{18%ounce}, half the oregano, and @Italian seasoning{2%tsp}. Cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from heat; transfer sausage to a #large bowl{}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @orzo pasta{6%ounce} and scallion whites; toss to coat. Cook, stirring often, until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, 1¾ cups water, and @Italian seasoning{2%tsp}. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has evaporated slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir grated zucchini into pan. Cook until zucchini is tender and orzo is al dente, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in half the sausage and @butter{1%tbsp}. Divide between #containers{}. Sprinkle with scallion greens and @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}. Keep refrigerated until ready to eat. Enjoy at room temperature or microwaved to reheat.

Place @flatbreads{2} on baking sheet used for zucchini. Evenly spread with remaining tomatoes; season with salt, pepper, and remaining @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}. Top with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}, broiled zucchini, and remaining sausage. Bake in oven until flatbreads are golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from oven and let rest ~{1-2%minutes}. Scatter with @chili flakes{1%tsp}(to taste) and remaining oregano. Cut into slices, then serve.

> The Lunch Italian Orzotto nutrition information is as follows: Calories: 840, Fat: 37 g, Saturated Fat: 17 g, Carbohydrate: 84 g, Sugar: 11 g, Fiber: 6 g, Protein: 42 g, Cholesterol: 180 mg, Sodium: 2000 mg. The nutrition facts panel below represents the nutrient values for the Chicken Sausage Flatbread Dinner.